        "created_at": "2023-05-10T08:59:11.298Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Yes it is. Since ACI is reused when you reregister you are joined to the group automatically. This is a personal gripe I have with Signal.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"anon88132\" data-post=\"6\" data-topic=\"53206\" data-full=\"true\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/ba9def/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> anon88132:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>you need ‚ÄúAuthCredential (for the new UID (user identity), which is new when someone else register the same number (from scratch) and the GroupMasterKey (only known by group members, not the server)‚Äù to interact with the group X (see <a href=\"https://signal.org/blog/signal-private-group-system/\">Signal &gt;&gt; Blog &gt;&gt; Technology Preview: Signal Private Group System</a> for more details)</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Except group admin will send it automatically if the user reregisters on safety number change. <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/rage.png?v=12\" title=\":rage:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":rage:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>",
