        "id": 214460,
        "name": "",
        "username": "TeeJay82",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/teejay82/{size}/1806_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-05-10T15:14:54.375Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"anon88132\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"53206\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/ba9def/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> anon88132:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>what is <code>removed their Signal account</code>?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I think so. They said that they‚Äôd stop using Signal. I suspect that it was automatically done upon removal of the app from their phone.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote group-volunteer_moderators\" data-username=\"Herohtar\" data-post=\"9\" data-topic=\"53206\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/herohtar/48/43780_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Herohtar:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>They could keep around a backup and restore it at a later point (assuming there are no incompatibilities with the current version of Signal), in which case you would expect group membership to be restored.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>How often would this actually happen in practice? I can‚Äôt fathom why someone would expect this to work this way. What else would one expect than to have to start from scratch if they remove their account somewhere?</p>",
        "post_number": 10,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 11,
        "updated_at": "2023-05-10T15:14:54.375Z",
