      {
        "id": 255199,
        "name": "",
        "username": "naught101",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/naught101/{size}/49509_2.png",
        "created_at": "2024-11-09T03:01:37.548Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I hit this problem, as described here: <a href=\"https://github.com/signalapp/Signal-Desktop/issues/2202#issuecomment-2463103392\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Deleted user from the group still receives messages ¬∑ Issue #2202 ¬∑ signalapp/Signal-Desktop ¬∑ GitHub</a></p>\n<p>We have a semi-sensitive group with 150 members. Some admins can see a bunch of these ‚Äúdead acount‚Äù group members (but each admin sees a different list). This is really disconcerting.</p>\n<p>I agree that if an account becomes deregistered, then it should be removed from a group, at least after a short period (a week?). If the account is deregistered longer than that, there is a chance that the account will be re-registered with the same phone number, but owned by a different person (this has happened in groups I‚Äôm in before). There is a ‚Äúsecurity number has changed‚Äù message, but those happen so often )when someone upgrades a phone or whatever) that most of them get ignored. It‚Äôs not possible from those messages to see that an account was deregisterd and then re-registered. This seems like a fairly large security hole.</p>\n<p>Even if we don‚Äôt get a fix to remove deregistered users automatically, it would be good to get a ‚Äúremove all deregistered users‚Äù button for admin to use, because manually removing 20-30 users from a large group is painful.</p>",
